在[[生物学|生物学]]中，'''再生'''是指由[[基因组|基因组]]、[[细胞|细胞]]、[[微生物|微生物]]和[[生态系统|生态系统]]对在自然环境下所造成的自身损伤的一种重建、恢复和发育的过程。从[[细菌|细菌]]到人类，任何物种都有再生能力<ref name="Carlson07">{{cite book | last=Carlson | first=B. M. | title=Principles of Regenerative Biology | year=2007 | publisher=Elsevier Inc. | pages=400 | url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/book/9780123694393 | isbn=978-0-12-369439-3 | access-date=2013-12-08 | archive-date=2016-10-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003130840/http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/book/9780123694393 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Gabor">{{cite journal | last1=Gabor | first1=M. H. | last2=Hotchkiss | first2=R. D. | title=Parameters governing bacterial regeneration and genetic recombination after fusion of Bacillus subtilis protoplasts | journal=Journal of Bacteriology | volume=137 | issue=3 | year=1979 | pages=1346–1353 | url=http://jb.asm.org/cgi/content/abstract/137/3/1346 | pmid=108246 | pmc=218319 | access-date=2013-12-08 | archive-date=2008-07-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080724211713/http://jb.asm.org/cgi/content/abstract/137/3/1346 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。再生可以是完全性再生<ref name=CompleteRegen>{{cite web | last1 = Min | first1 = Su | last2 = Wang | first2 = Song W. | last3 = Orr | first3 = William | title = Graphic general pathology: 2.2 complete regeneration: | work = Pathology | publisher = pathol.med.stu.edu.cn | year = 2006 | quote = (1) Complete regeneration: The new tissue is the same as the tissue that was lost. After the repair process has been completed, the structure and function of the injured tissue are completely normal | url = http://pathol.med.stu.edu.cn/pathol/listEngContent2.aspx?ContentID=492 | accessdate = 2012-12-07 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121207231322/http://pathol.med.stu.edu.cn/pathol/listEngContent2.aspx?ContentID=492 | archivedate = 2012-12-07 }}</ref>，即损伤后由周围同种细胞来修复<ref name=CompleteRegen/>，或者是不完全性再生<ref name=InCompleteRegen>{{cite web | last1 = Min | first1 = Su | last2 = Wang | first2 = Song W. | last3 = Orr | first3 = William | title = Graphic general pathology: 2.3 Incomplete regeneration: | work = Pathology | publisher = pathol.med.stu.edu.cn | year = 2006 | quote = The new tissue is not the same as the tissue that was lost. After the repair process has been completed, there is a loss in the structure or function of the injured tissue. In this type of repair, it is common that granulation tissue (stromal connective tissue) proliferates to fill the defect created by the necrotic cells. The necrotic cells are then replaced by scar tissue. | url = http://pathol.med.stu.edu.cn/pathol/listEngContent2.aspx?contentID=493 | accessdate = 2012-12-07 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131110180450/http://pathol.med.stu.edu.cn/pathol/listEngContent2.aspx?contentID=493 | archivedate = 2013-11-10 }}</ref>，即损伤后坏死组织由纤维结缔组织来修复<ref name=InCompleteRegen/>。在再生开始阶段，再生是由[[DNA复制|DNA合成]]的分子过程介导的<ref name="Himeno92">{{cite journal | last1=Himeno | first1=Y. | last2=Engelman | first2=R. W. | last3=Good | first3=R. A. | title=Influence of calorie restriction on oncogene expression and DNA synthesis during liver regeneration | journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America | volume=89 | issue=12 | year=1992 | pages=5497–5501 | doi=10.1073/pnas.89.12.5497| pmid=1608960 | pmc=49319}}</ref><ref name="Bryant88">{{cite journal | last1=Bryant | first1=P. J. | last2=Fraser | first2=S. E. | title=Wound healing, cell communication, and DNA synthesis during imaginal disc regeneration in Drosophila | journal=Developmental Biology | volume=127 | issue=1 | year=1988 | pmid=2452103 | pages=197–208 | doi=10.1016/0012-1606(88)90201-1 | url=http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/0012160688902011 | access-date=2013-12-08 | archive-date=2018-12-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215172333/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/0012160688902011 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。生物学中的再生主要是指多细胞生物通过修复及保持他们的生理和形态的完整性的一种[[性狀|性狀]]。再生从根本上说是由基因调节的无性细胞过程<ref name="Brokes08">{{cite journal | doi=10.1146/annurev.cellbio.24.110707.175336?select23=Choose | last1=Brokes | first1=J. P. | last2=Kumar | first2=A. | title=Comparative Aspects of Animal Regeneration | journal=Annu. Rev. Cell Dev. Biol. | volume=28 | pages=525–549 | url=http://www.annualreviews.org/doi/full/10.1146/annurev.cellbio.24.110707.175336?select23=Choose}}</ref>。再生不同于[[繁殖|繁殖]]。举例来说，[[水螅|水螅]]通过[[出芽生殖|出芽生殖]]的方式进行再生而不是繁殖。

[[水蛭|水蛭]]与[[涡虫|涡虫]]长期作为具有极强[[适应|适应]]性的再生能力的模型生物<ref name="Sánchez00">{{cite journal | doi=10.1002/(SICI)1521-1878(200006)22:6<578::AID-BIES11>3.0.CO;2-# | last1=Sánchez | first1=A. A. | title=Regeneration in the metazoans: why does it happen? | journal=BioEssays | volume=22 | issue=6 | pages=578–590 | url=http://planaria.neuro.utah.edu/publications/BioEssays.pdf | year=2000 | pmid=10842312 | author= | access-date=2013-12-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111154356/http://planaria.neuro.utah.edu/publications/BioEssays.pdf | archive-date=2013-11-11 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。一旦受伤，他们的细胞就被激活，并开始修复组织及器官回到初始状态<ref name="Reddien04">{{cite journal | doi=10.1146/annurev.cellbio.20.010403.095114 | last1=Reddien | first1=P. W. | last2=Alvarado | first2=A. S. | title=Fundamentals of planarian regenerations | journal=Annual Review of Cell and Developmental Biology | volume=20 | pages=725–757 | url=http://www.annualreviews.org/doi/abs/10.1146/annurev.cellbio.20.010403.095114 | year=2004 | pmid=15473858 | access-date=2013-12-08 | archive-date=2022-02-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220222022754/https://www.annualreviews.org/doi/abs/10.1146/annurev.cellbio.20.010403.095114 }}</ref>。[[两栖动物|两栖动物]]中的其中一[[目_(生物)|目]][[有尾目|有尾目]]（如[[蝾螈|蝾螈]]），很可能是[[脊椎动物|脊椎动物]]中再生能力最强的生物，其四肢、尾、爪、眼睛和各种内部结构都有很强的再生能力<ref name="Carlson07" />。器官的再生是[[动物|多细胞动物]]中一种常见和广泛的适应能力<ref name="Sánchez00" />。在相关条件下，一些动物可以通过[[断裂生殖|断裂]]、[[出芽生殖|出芽]]或[[分裂_(生物学)|分裂]]的方式进行[[无性生殖|无性生殖]]<ref name="Brokes08" />。比如涡虫，首先通过中间部份的收缩、分割分裂成两半，并且每一半形成一个新的个体，成为原始的[[克隆|克隆]]<ref name="Cambell96">{{cite book | last=Campbell | first=N. A. | title=Biology | year=2002 | url=https://archive.org/details/biology0000camp_6 | edition=4th | publisher=The Benjamin Cummings Publishing Company, Inc. | place=California | pages=[https://archive.org/details/biology0000camp_6/page/n1206 1206]}}</ref>。[[棘皮动物|棘皮动物]]（如海星）、小龙虾，以及许多爬行动物和两栖动物有着很强的再生能力。一个很典型的例子就是[[自割|自割]]，当动物察觉到危机时，会主动分离肢体或尾巴，以避免被捕获。肢体或尾巴自断后，断处细胞开始进行修复，组织将重新生成<ref name="Wilkie01">{{cite journal | last=Wilkie | first=I. | title=Autotomy as a prelude to regeneration in echinoderms | journal=Microscopy Research and Technique | volume=55 | issue=6 | pages=369–396 | year=2001 | pmid=11782069 | doi=10.1002/jemt.1185}}</ref><ref name="Maiorana77">{{cite journal | last=Maiorana | first=V. C. | title=Tail autotomy, functional conflicts and their resolution by a salamander | journal=Nature | volume=2265 | issue=5594 | pages=533–535 | year=1977 | doi=10.1038/265533a0}}</ref><ref name="Maginnis06">{{cite journal | last=Maginnis | first=T. L. | title=The costs of autotomy and regeneration in animals: a review and framework for future research | journal=Behavioural Ecology | volume=7 | issue=5 | pages=857–872 | year=2006 | doi=10.1093/beheco/arl010 | url=http://beheco.oxfordjournals.org/content/17/5/857.full | access-date=2013-12-08 | archive-date=2015-12-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151205031951/http://beheco.oxfordjournals.org/content/17/5/857.full | dead-url=no }}</ref>。生态系统也同样可以再生。如在森林火灾或者病虫害爆发之时，一些[[先鋒物種|先鋒物種]]会占据并争夺生存空间，从而开拓他们新的栖息地。在[[生态学|生态学]]中，这种新的生长方式被称作再生<ref name="Dietze08">{{cite journal | doi=10.1890/07-0271.1 | last1=Dietze | first1=M. C. | last2=Clark | first2=J. S. | title=Changing the gap dynamics paradigm: Vegetative regenerative control on forest response to disturbance | journal=Ecological Monographs | volume=78 | issue=3 | pages=331–347 | url=http://coweeta.uga.edu/publications/10300.pdf | year=2008 | access-date=2013-12-08 | archive-date=2010-06-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100610074913/http://coweeta.uga.edu/publications/10300.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Bailey02">{{cite journal | doi=10.1016/S0378-1127(01)00564-3 | last1=Bailey | first1=J. D. | last2=Covington | first2=W. W. | title=Evaluation ponderosa pine regeneration rates following ecological restoration treatments in northern Arizona, USA | journal=Forest Ecology and Management | volume=155 | pages=271–278 | url=http://library.eri.nau.edu/gsdl/collect/erilibra/index/assoc/HASH0e9a.dir/doc.pdf | year=2002 | access-date=2013-12-08 | archive-date=2013-11-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111153241/http://library.eri.nau.edu/gsdl/collect/erilibra/index/assoc/HASH0e9a.dir/doc.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==细胞基础==
在细胞损伤后，多细胞生物的组织结构形成是由{{link-en|基因表达调控|Regulation of gene expression}}所决定。神经细胞释放一些与快速生长相关的蛋白质，如{{link-en|Gap-43蛋白|Gap-43 protein}}、[[微管蛋白|微管蛋白]]、[[肌动蛋白|肌动蛋白]]以及数组[[神经肽|神经肽]]和[[细胞因子|细胞因子]]从而诱导损伤细胞生理反应从而再生<ref name="Fu97">{{cite journal | last1=Fu | first1=S. Y. | last2=Gordon | first2=T. | title=The cellular and molecular basis of peripheral nerve regeneration | journal=Molecular Neurobiology | volume=14 | issue=1–2 | pages=67–116 | year=1997 | pmid=9170101 | doi=10.1007/BF02740621 | url=http://www.springerlink.com/content/675770336wq42078/ }}{{Dead link|date=2020年2月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>。许多参与的基因在组织的原始再生中被重新激活。在[[斑马鱼|斑马鱼]]的原基细胞中，再生过程由''msx''家族的4个同源异形基因所调控<ref name="akimenko96">{{cite journal | last1=Akimenko | first1=M.  | last2=Johnson | first2=S. L. | last3=Wseterfield | first3=M. | last4=Ekker | first4=M. | title=Differential induction of four ''msx'' homeobox genes during fin development and regeneration in zebrafish | journal=Development | volume=121 | issue=2 | pages=347–357 | url=http://dev.biologists.org/content/121/2/347.full.pdf | year=1996 | pmid=7768177}}</ref>。

==组织==
“使用成年人的[[体细胞|体]][[干细胞|干细胞]]的去分化或/和转分化细胞，包括组织结构预先重新排列的规则，可以在相同动物的不同组织中表达并重建出与周围相适应的组织极性、结构和形式<ref name="Alvarado06">{{cite journal | last1=Alvarado | first1=A. S. | last2=Tsonis | first2=P. A. | title=Bridging the regeneration gap: genetic insights from diverse animal models | journal=Nat. Rev. Genet. | volume=7 | issue=11 | pages=873–884 | year=2006 | pmid=17047686 | doi=10.1038/nrg1923 | url=http://planaria.neuro.utah.edu/publications/NRG2006.pdf | author= | access-date=2013-12-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110103049/http://planaria.neuro.utah.edu/publications/NRG2006.pdf | archive-date=2013-11-10 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>{{rp|873}}。”在该发育过程中，基因被重新激活用于改变不同组织的[[分化能|分化能]]的性质。发育及再生涉及到把细胞群协调及组织成{{link-en|胚基|blastema}}（干细胞再生开始时的细胞基团<ref name="Kumar07">{{cite journal | last1=Kumar | first1=A. | last2=Godwin | first2=J. W. | last3=Gates | first3=P. B. | last4=Garza-Garcia | first4=A. A. | last5=Brokes | first5=J. P. | title= Molecular Basis for the Nerve Dependence of Limb Regeneration in an Adult Vertebrate | journal = Science | volume=318 | issue=5851 | pages=772–7 | year=2007 | pmid=17975060 | pmc=2696928 | doi=10.1126/science.1147710 }}</ref>）。细胞的去分化意味着他们在再生过程中失去了那些组织特异性的功能。不应该同转分化混淆，转分化指的是细胞在再生过程中失去了其组织特异性，然后重新分化成不同类型的细胞<ref name="Alvarado06" />。

==两侧对称动物==
[[涡虫|涡虫]]再生能力极强。举例来说，涡虫可以纵向或者横向分裂成两个不同个体。在一项科学实验中，T. H. Morgan发现，涡虫只需要其1/279一块即可以成功再生为一个新的蠕虫。这个大小（约10,000个细胞）通常被认为是涡虫可再生为一个新的个体的最小片段。涡虫的再生属于割处再生，即截断后，断处的细胞形成胚基。

===脊椎动物===

====两栖动物====
一些简单点的动物如{{link-en|花虫类动物|planarian}}具有很强的再生能力。因为拥有需要长时间保持自己的身体形态免遭破坏而随时起作用的干细胞（neoblast）。受伤后，他们会分裂和分化出缺少的组织和器官。这个过程在脊椎动物里要复杂得多，但尽管如此，[[蝾螈|蝾螈]]断肢后仍有很强大的再生能力。蝾螈的肢体再生已经被作为一个课题被广泛研究中。

蝾螈的肢体再生主要分为2个步骤，首先成熟细胞去[[细胞分化|分化]]成类似胚胎[[干细胞|干细胞]]的状态，其次这些细胞[[发育生物学|发育]]成新的组织<ref name="odelberg">{{cite journal | pmid = 15314652 | doi=10.1371/journal.pbio.0020232 | volume=2 | issue=8 | title=Unraveling the Molecular Basis for Regenerative Cellular Plasticity | pmc=509298 | pages=E232 | author=Odelberg SJ | journal = PLoS Biology|date=August 2004}}</ref>。 

肢体断掉后，在不到12小时内，表皮会增生覆盖断枝的截断面，形成所谓的顶端上皮帽（AEC）。在接下来的几天时间里，残存的细胞去分化形成{{link-en|胚基|blastema}}（大量去分化增殖的细胞）。随着胚基的形成，一些用于形成[[胚胎|胚胎]]的基因，如[[同源框|Hox]]A与HoxD被激活<ref name="bryant">{{cite journal | pmid = 12455626 | volume=46 | issue=7 | title=Vertebrate limb regeneration and the origin of limb stem cells | year=2002 | pages=887–96 | author=Bryant SV, Endo T, Gardiner DM | journal = The International journal of developmental biology}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | pmid = 8951064 | volume=122 | issue=11 | title=Nerve dependency of regeneration: the role of Distal-less and FGF signaling in amphibian limb regeneration | pages=3487–97 | author=Mullen LM, Bryant SV, Torok MA, Blumberg B, Gardiner DM | journal = Development (Cambridge, England)|date=November 1996}}</ref>。肢体的[[人体解剖学方位|远端]]（如手或脚）尖端形成第一个胚基。而在其中间部位随着胚基的发育逐渐被填充<ref name="odelberg" /><ref name="bryant" />。肢体的[[运动神经元|运动神经元]]、肌肉和血管再生，并与断枝相匹配。整个过程的时间随着生物年龄的不同而有所变化，成熟个体肢体功能完全恢复的时间大约为一个月到三个月时间。 

尽管历史上只有少数人员从事研究肢体再生的工作，但最近已经把作为基因模型生物的蝾螈（''Ambystoma mexicanum''）进行研究取得重大进展。这一进展已经促进了[[基因组学|基因组学]]，[[生物信息学|生物信息学]]、[[体细胞|体细胞]][[遗传子导入|遗传子导入]]及其他领域的发展，也创造了重要生物学特性进步的机会，如在蝾螈上发现的肢体再生<ref>{{cite journal | pmid = 15136146 | doi=10.1016/j.ydbio.2004.02.016 | volume=270 | issue=1 | title=A stepwise model system for limb regeneration | pages=135–45 | author=Endo T, Bryant SV, Gardiner DM | journal = Developmental Biology|date=June 2004}}</ref>。钝口螈的遗传资源保藏和利用中心（AGSC）是由[[国家科学基金会|美国国家科学基金会]]支持的对蝾螈的再生、繁殖所进行研究的一个组织。该组织位于肯塔基的大学，AGSC是专门为在美国各地和国外供应以良好基因为特点的蝾螈的胚胎、幼虫和成熟个体的实验室。[[國立衛生研究院_(美國)|美国国立卫生研究院]]资助了该项蝾基因组计划（SGP），且已建立第一个以两栖动物基因图谱和附加因子为主的数据基地，并建设了研究界的门户网站<ref>http://www.ambystoma.org {{Wayback|url=http://www.ambystoma.org/ |date=20201006031601 }} Sal-Site website</ref> 。

